cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of parsing biological images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach presented in the paper involves the use of deep neural networks (cs.LG) and optimization techniques (cs.AI) to disentangle groups of organisms in the images. The method also involves the use of vectorial descriptors (cs.NE) to match local image patches to a gallery of isolated elements. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applicability of the approach to a wider class of image parsing problems, which could fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
